24 for such training that the board of trustees of a school district may to use to satisfy
25 the requirements of section 1. Section 2 of this bill makes a conforming change to
26 apply the existing definition of “professional development training” to the
27 provisions of section 1.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 391A of NRS is hereby amended by
2 adding thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The board of trustees of each school district shall ensure
4 that, not later than 30 days after the first day of instruction of each
5 school year, and such additional times throughout the year
6 thereafter as the board of trustees deems appropriate, each staff
7 member, including, without limitation, each teacher, administrator
8 and education support professional, receives professional
9 development training in best practices for:
10 (a) Addressing the behavior of pupils;
11 (b) Fostering a positive school climate;
12 (c) Positive behavioral interventions and support;
13 (d) Conflict resolution;
14 (e) De-escalation techniques; and
15 (f) Classroom management.
16 2. The Department shall coordinate with each regional
17 training program to develop curricula for professional
18 development training that the board of trustees of a school district
19 may use to provide the professional development training required
20 pursuant to subsection 1.
21 3. The board of trustees of each school district shall, on or
22 before August 1 of each year, prepare a report that describes any
23 professional development training provided pursuant to subsection
24 1 during the previous year, how the school district ensured that
25 such professional development training was provided and each
26 date on which such professional development training was
27 provided, and submit the report to the Director of the Legislative
28 Counsel Bureau for transmittal to:
29 (a) In even-numbered years, the next regular session of the
30 Legislature; and
31 (b) In odd-numbered years, the Joint Interim Standing
32 Committee on Education.
33 4. As used in this section:
